column169: Dayton Freight observed approximately one (1) gallon of material released from one (1) 5-gallon metal pail due to a forklift puncture. The released material impacted the trailer floor. Dayton Freight personnel cleaned the impacted area with granular absorbents. The spent absorbents were gathered, and the recovered material and damaged pail was containerized into one (1) 55-gallon poly drum. The generated waste was staged onsite at the terminal in a secure location. The generated waste will remain onsite for Dayton Freight’s contracted hazardous waste vendor to coordinate disposal.

column169: DURING NORMAL HANDLING PROCESS AT THE UPS HONG KONG INTERNATIONAL CHEK LAP KOK FACILITY ONE AIR PACKAGE FROM HONG KONG DESTINED TO THE USA WAS OBSERVED SMOKING ON THE BELT. THE PACKAGE WAS IMMEDIATELY TAKEN AWAY FROM THE BELT AND PLACED IN A SEGREGATED AREA. THE SMOLDERING INCREASED AND SUBSEQUENTLY THE PACKAGE BEGAN BURNING. UPS STAFF USED A FIRE EXTINGUISHER TO EXTINGUISH THE FIRE. THE EVENT WAS DISCOVERED PRIOR TO THE PACKAGE BEING LOADED INTO AN AIR CONTAINER. THE PACKAGE HAD PASSED A DANGEROUS GOODS ACCEPTANCE AUDIT PRIOR TO THE LITHIUM BATTERY INCIDENT. THE PACKAGE WAS FULLY DECLARED WITH AN APPROPRIATE IATA SHIPPERS DECLARATION AS UN3480 LITHIUM ION BATTERIES, SECTION IA OF PACKING INSTRUCTION 965. AFTER THE EVENT WAS EXTINGUISHED, THE OPERATIONS NOTED THE INNER THREE BATTERIES WERE NOT PROPERLY SEPARATED OR PROTECTED. ADDITIONALLY, NO WATT HOUR MARKINGS WERE FOUND ON THE BATTERIES.  PER 49CFR 171.15, THE NATIONAL RESPONSE CENTER WAS CONTACTED BY TELEPHONE TO REPORT THE INCIDENT. THE OFFICER WAS UNABLE TO ACCEPT THE TELEPHONE REPORT DUE TO THE EVENT NOT OCCURRING IN THE USA.
PACKAGE FOUND CRUSHED IN THE UNLOAD, RESPONDER TRANSPORTED TO THE DMP FOR PROCESSING.

MISALIGNED SAFETY CAP ALLOWING LEAKAGE TO OCCUR SOILING ALL BOTTLES IN A CORROSIVE LIQUID.

Exterior packaging was wet on one side and on the underside by a thick clear liquid that came from the inside of the package. Inside the 4G box are 4 quantities of 1 gallon plastic bottles containing SEK-Surebond SB-8700 Wet Look Joint Stabilizing Sealer with Anti-fungal. One of the bottles had a streak of liquid leaked on to its body that is coming from under the cap. When the cap was opened, the seal was opened a quarter of the way. The liquid leaked inside the exterior packaging and hardened in an hour. The rest of the bottles were unharmed.
